1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:03,013
There are different ways to define functions in JavaScript

2
00:00:03,212 --> 00:00:05,000
including function declarations

3
00:00:05,263 --> 00:00:06,450
function expressions

4
00:00:06,725 --> 00:00:07,925
and arrow functions

5
00:00:08,988 --> 00:00:11,762
Each syntax has its own use cases and benefits

6
00:00:12,875 --> 00:00:15,725
Function declarations are hoisted to the top of their scope

7
00:00:16,113 --> 00:00:18,550
allowing them to be called before being defined

8
00:00:18,800 --> 00:00:21,125
whereas function expressions are not hoisted

